6 An Act relating to groundwater use; amending 82 O.S.
2021, Section 1020.17, which relates to spacing
7 rules; conforming statutory reference; removing
requirement for certain public hearing; authorizing
8 adoption of certain spacing; and providing an
effective date.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 82 O.S. 2021, Section 1020.17, is
13 amended to read as follows:
14 Section 1020.17. The Oklahoma Water Resources Board may
15 promulgate rules under Article I of the Administrative Procedures
16 Act which establish a proper spacing of wells which, in its
17 judgment, is necessary to an orderly withdrawal of water in relation
18 to the allocation, by regular permits and temporary permits, of
19 water to the land overlying the basin or subbasin. The Board shall
20 conduct at least one public hearing at a location within or in close
21 proximity to each major basin or subbasin before adopting rules
22 establishing well spacing for such basin or subbasin may adopt
23 specific spacing for each basin as part of establishing a maximum
24 annual yield pursuant to Section 1020.6 of this title.
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1509 Page 1

1 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
2 Passed the Senate the 25th day of March, 2026.
